# Retro "Pokémon FireRed" Style Web UI & Backend Integration

The AI Study Companion has been successfully transformed into a full-stack gamified application!

## 1. Homepage & Animated Background
A responsive `<HomePage />` was added as the initial landing screen:
- **Design Elements**: Retro styling with pixel-perfect typography (`Press Start 2P`).
- **RetroBackground Animation**: A custom CSS keyframe animation looping 8-bit clouds drifting horizontally across the "sky" and a grassy landscape texture scrolling seamlessly across the bottom. This acts as a subtle, nostalgic base layer that doesn’t distract from the core text.
- **Routing**: Pressing the pulsing "START LEARNING" button transitions the view into the main dashboard application.

## 2. API Wiring (React to FastAPI)
The simulated dummy data in the React app has been stripped out. The frontend now communicates directly with the Python `backend/` using the new [api.js](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/OneDrive/Desktop/ai%20learn/ai-study-companion/frontend-retro/src/api.js) fetch layer:

*   **Top HUD state**: On load, [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/OneDrive/Desktop/ai%20learn/ai-study-companion/frontend-retro/src/App.jsx) immediately calls the backend `/progress/retro-student` endpoint to grab the latest `total_points` (mapped to visual XP and Coins), player Level, and achieved badges from the SQLite database.
*   **Chat Tutor**: User inputs in the Chat Tutor now trigger a `POST /explain` to the backend. The actual OpenAI/LLM response is returned and rendered in the RPG dialogue box.
*   **Quiz Battle**:
    *   Starting a quiz battle calls `POST /quiz` internally fetching unique questions dynamically. 
    *   Answering the quiz questions tracks selections, and upon finishing, sends a `POST /quiz/submit` to process the score, officially level up the character in DB, and mint any new Badges!

## Run the Fully Functional App

To test everything end-to-end:

1. **Start the Backend server** (from the project root):
   ```bash
   python -m uvicorn backend.main:app --reload
   ```
2. **Start the Frontend development server** (from `frontend-retro/`):
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```
3.  Open `http://localhost:5173/` in your browser. Start on the new Homepage, admire the looping clouds, and launch into the fully functional AI concept chat and quizzes!
